Bland Altman analysis of two methods Notebook

This documents the code for performing a Bland-Altman analysis of two methods, and preparing graphs illustrating the results. It relies on the blandr package, as well as tidyverse and ggplot2 Created KPI Feb 20, 2020

library (tidyverse)
library (blandr)
# Create dataframe and extract specific data for Bland Altman analysis
MT <- read.csv("/Volumes/InmanDrive4/Dropbox/Dropbox/KPI/University_of_Dundee/Dissertation/Data/Output_files/AllResults_Data/AllResults_Table.csv")
MT$TotDNA <- as.factor(MT$TotDNA) # Need to turn the TotDNA into a factor (rather than integer) in order to plot using it as a group in ggplot (integer can't be used to group values, unless binning them). Before writing this step, I got an error in later code that MT$DNA did not exist, which of course it did. Finally realized you can't group by integers.

Subset dataframe with LR from one program (including columns needed for the subsetting task)

rr baEFM <- MT %>%

select(Sample,Program,TotlogLR,StFilt,TCon,TotDNA) %>% filter(Program == ,StFilt ==,TCon == ) baEFM <- na.omit(baEFM) # Subset dataframe with LR from the other program (including columns needed for the subsetting task) baLTD <- MT %>%

select(Sample,Program,TotlogLR,StFilt,TCon,TotDNA) %>% filter(Program == ,StFilt == , TCon == ) baLTD <- na.omit(baLTD)

Merge subsetted dataframes into one for Bland Altman calculations

rr ba <- baEFM %>%

inner_join(baLTD, by = ) %>% select(Sample,TotlogLR.x,TotlogLR.y,TotDNA.x,TotDNA.y)

Check on data to ensure integrity and adherence to proper format

rr blandr.data.preparation(ba\(TotlogLR.x, ba\)TotlogLR.y, sig.level = 0.95) r #Prepares statistics used in calculating the Bland-Altman plots for methods Lab Retriever and likeLTD) bland.stats <- blandr.statistics(ba\(TotlogLR.x, ba\)TotlogLR.y)

Standard bland altman plot, using the script from the blandr package

rr blandr.draw(ba\(TotlogLR.x, ba\)TotlogLR.y, method1name = , method2name = , plotTitle = -Altman plot: EFM/likeLTD Total logLR stutter off, sig.level = 0.95, LoA.mode = 1, annotate = FALSE, ciDisplay = TRUE, ciShading = TRUE, normalLow = FALSE, normalHigh = FALSE, lowest_y_axis = FALSE, highest_y_axis = FALSE, point_size = 0.8, overlapping = FALSE, plotter = 2, x.plot.mode = , y.plot.mode = , plotProportionalBias = FALSE, plotProportionalBias.se = TRUE, assume.differences.are.normal = TRUE)

Various plot options using ggplot; can use in addition to or separate from the blandr.draw function

Scatter plot with 4 plots, one for each amount of Total DNA (TotDNA) of the sample

rr ggplot(ba, aes(x = bland.stats\(means, y = bland.stats\)differences)) + geom_point() + geom_text(aes(label=Sample), hjust=2, color = ) + facet_wrap(~ TotDNA.y) + labs(title = -Altman plot /likeLTD stutter off, x = , y = ) ggsave(_facet_pts.pdf, width = 13, height = 10)

rr #+ # theme_bw()

Scatter plot with single plot, each amount of TotDNA color-coded

rr ggplot(data = ba) + geom_point(mapping = aes(x = bland.stats\(means, y = bland.stats\)differences, color = TotDNA.y)) + labs(title = -Altman plot /likeLTD stutter off, x = , y = ) + theme_bw()

Smoothed plots of 4 DNA amounts (not that informative)

rr ggplot(data = ba) + geom_smooth(mapping = aes(x = bland.stats\(means, y = bland.stats\)differences, color = TotDNA.y), show.legend = TRUE) + labs(title = -Altman plot /likeLTD stutter off, x = , y = ) + theme_bw()

All data with a single smoothed line, with TotDNA color-coded

rr ggplot(data = ba, mapping = aes(x = bland.stats\(means, y = bland.stats\)differences)) + geom_point(mapping = aes(color = TotDNA.y, shape = TotDNA.y)) + geom_smooth() + labs(title = -Altman plot /likeLTD stutter off, x = , y = ) + theme_bw()

All data with points plotted and smoothed line for each amt of TotDNA

rr ggplot(data = ba, mapping = aes(x = bland.stats\(means, y = bland.stats\)differences)) + geom_point(mapping = aes(color = TotDNA.y, shape = TotDNA.y)) + geom_smooth(mapping = aes(x = bland.stats\(means, y = bland.stats\)differences, color = TotDNA.y), show.legend = TRUE) + labs(title = -Altman plot /likeLTD stutter off, x = , y = ) + theme_bw()

4 plots, one for each amt of TotDNA, including smooth line, color, and shapes

rr ggplot(data = ba, mapping = aes(x = bland.stats\(means, y = bland.stats\)differences)) + geom_point(mapping = aes(color = TotDNA.y, shape = TotDNA.y)) + geom_smooth(mapping = aes(x = bland.stats\(means, y = bland.stats\)differences, color = TotDNA.y), show.legend = TRUE) + facet_wrap(~ TotDNA.y) + labs(title = -Altman plot /likeLTD stutter off, x = , y = ) + theme_bw()
